Two men sustained moderate injuries after a truck rolled over in Chris Hani Road near the N2 in Avoca. Durban Metropolitan Police, Greenwood Park SAPS, eThekwini Fire and Rescue, Specialised Tactical Accident Rescue Team (START) and KZN VIP were on scene. According to Shawn Herbst of Netcare 911, reports indicate that a driver of a heavy motor vehicle transporting cement lost control resulting in the rollover. “The patients were treated on scene and once stabilised were transported by ambulance to hospital,” said Herbst.